						               													<description>From the game box:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Q: Do you know a county like Vietnam?&amp;#10;A: Yes, of course!&amp;#10;Q: Can you show this on the map?&amp;#10;A: .... eee I....wait wait...&amp;#10;Q: Did you know that 87 million people live there?&amp;#10;A: ...OK...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Board game that you are holding is made for getting knowledge about geopolitical in a fun way and to spend time in a great way.&amp;#10;World is full of amazing stuff, look around and compare countries by size, population, economy and power - it makes you think.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You goal is to answer and show correct placement and collect 5 cards from each continent.&amp;#10;Game lasts until one player has collected 5 cards from each continent, or if each country is claimed by someone or is the game gets boring, then the ones who has most cards is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn you roll two dice. One dice shows which of the continents you have to choose from (6 is free choice) and the other dice shows how many countries you can try for this turn. Then player collects 1 or more cards from the corresponding card pack and sets himself ready. Then 2 minute timer is activated and active players must show with small tokens where each of those selected countries are.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are many many optional rules for game play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
